{{Beauty pageant | winner = [[Frances Marie Burke]] | represented = [[File:Flag of Philadelphia, Pennsylvania.svg|22px]] [[Philadelphia]] | date = September 7, 1940 | presenters = [[Bob Russell (entertainer)]] | entrants = 44 | placements = 15 | venue = [[Boardwalk Hall]], [[Atlantic City]], [[New Jersey]] | broadcaster = }}'''Miss America 1940''', the 14th [[Miss America]] pageant, was held at the [[Boardwalk Hall]] in [[Atlantic City, New Jersey]] on September 7, 1940.<ref>{{cite news|title=Miss America 1940 Says Two Sisters Are Prettier|last=Associated Press|date=1940-09-09|publisher=Oshkosh Daily Northwestern|page=7}}</ref> Aside from the 1940 winning entrant, two other contestants from [[Pennsylvania]] placed among the Top 15, one representing Eastern PA and the other from Western PA.
